Operations related to withdrawal management

List Withdrawals

GET
https://platform.arpdigital.io/services/api/v1
/withdrawals

Retrieve withdrawals for the authenticated organization

List Withdrawals › query Parameters

status
string · enum

Filter by withdrawal status

Enum values:
PROCESSING
COMPLETED
FAILED
limit
integer · min: 1 · max: 100

Maximum number of results (1-100, default 50)

Default: 50
offset
integer · min: 0

Number of results to skip (default 0)

Default: 0

List Withdrawals › Headers

X-Environment
string · enum · required

Specifies the environment to use (sandbox or production). This determines which database the API interacts with.

Enum values:
sandbox
production
Default: sandbox

Create Withdrawal

POST
https://platform.arpdigital.io/services/api/v1
/withdrawals

Create a new withdrawal for the authenticated organization

Create Withdrawal › Headers

X-Environment
string · enum · required

Specifies the environment to use (sandbox or production). This determines which database the API interacts with.

Enum values:
sandbox
production
Default: sandbox

Create Withdrawal › Request Body

currency
string · required

Currency code

amount
number · double · required

Withdrawal amount (must be positive)

destinationWalletId
string | null · uuid

Destination wallet ID (XOR with destinationBankAccountId)

destinationBankAccountId
string | null · uuid

Destination bank account ID (XOR with destinationWalletId)

cryptocurrencyId
string

Required when using destinationWalletId

notes
string

Optional notes

reference
string

Optional reference number

source
string · enum

Optional source of the withdrawal

Enum values:
API
WEB
MANUAL_ENTRY
externalReference
string | null

Optional external reference
